# Census of standard simply connected PL 4-manifolds, with VERBATIM Regina
# 4-manifold isomorphism signatures from:
#
#   J. Spreer and S. Tillmann, "The Trisection Genus of Standard Simply
#   Connected PL 4-Manifolds", Proc. SoCG 2018, LIPIcs vol. 99, article 71,
#   Appendix A.  (journal version: Experimental Mathematics 31(3), 2022;
#   arXiv:1712.04915)
#
# Each triangulation comes from a simple crystallisation and admits 15
# ts-tricolourings; the minimum central-surface genus equals the manifold's
# second Betti number, which is its trisection genus:  S4 -> 0, CP2 -> 1,
# S2xS2 -> 2  (and K3 -> 22; see the note at the bottom).
#
# Format:  <label>|<Regina dim-4 isomorphism signature>
# Load (Regina build):
#   bhrt-bench --census data/spreer_tillmann.esig --known data/known_trisection_genus.txt

# S^4 -- 15 ts-tricolourings of types (0;0,0,0)x10, (1;1,0,0)x4, (2;1,1,0)x1
# (Spreer-Tillmann SoCG 2018, Section 3.2 + Appendix A). min genus = 0.
S4|gLAAMQbbcddeffffaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa

# CP^2 -- unique 8-pentachoron simple crystallisation. trisection genus = 1.
CP2|iLvLQQQkbghhghhfffggfaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa

# S^2 x S^2 -- 14-pentachoron simple crystallisation. trisection genus = 2.
S2xS2|oLvMPLQAPMQPkbfgghjihhiilkkmllmnnnnaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa

# K3 surface -- 134-pentachoron simple crystallisation; trisection genus = 22
# (Spreer-Tillmann SoCG 2018, Theorem 1). The isomorphism signature is ~700
# characters long; it is deliberately NOT inlined here to avoid any silent
# transcription error in its long padding tail. To include K3, copy the
# signature verbatim from the paper's Appendix A (delete the newlines first,
# as the paper instructs) and append a line:
#   K3|<that-signature>
